ccretion-based model for filament\nevolution in the local neighbourhood (D<500pc). Structures located in the\nhighest backgrounds develop the highest central Av, Mcore, and Mwing as Mtot\nincreases with time, favoured by the local availability of material and the\nenhanced gravitational potential. Our results indicate that filaments acquiring\na significantly massive central region with Mcore>Mcrit/2 may become\nsupercritical and form stars. This translates into a need for filaments to\nbecome at least moderately self-gravitating in order to undergo localised star\nformation or become star-forming filaments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Mar 2016 13:21:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-22"}
